result.execSummary:
The defendant Clayton Warichak was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case.

  • Disorderly Conduct [Modifiers: Domestic Abuse, Domestic Abuse Repeater], an unclassified felony, Wisconsin Statutes 947.01(1).

Charge(s) in this case were read in to this or other case(s). A "read in" charge is a charge that is dismissed as part of a plea agreement, however:

  • The defendant agrees to have the court consider the charge(s) when sentencing for another crime, under Wis. Stats. 973.20(1g)(b); and
  • The defendant cannot be prosecuted for these charge(s) in the future.

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

Case called at 1:50 pm [Clerk SH] (Case was scheduled for STC)
[Reserve Judge Robert Mawdsley presiding for BrIV]
Defendant Clayton Warichak in court, in custody, on Huber release from Ozaukee County, with Attorney Elizabeth F Svehlek. ADA Jeffrey M. Shock appeared for the State of Wisconsin.

Constitutional rights reviewed; maximum penalties recited; plea of "No Contest" entered on Count #3; factual basis stipulated; victim rights compliance verified; Court finds the plea has been entered freely, voluntarily, intelligently and accepts the plea, finds the Defendant  guilty, and orders JOC entered.
On Motion of the State, the Court reads-in and dismisses Counts #1 & #2

On Count #3, the Court sentences Mr. Warichak to 2 years, with an Initial Term of Confinement in Prison of 18 months, and the maximum time to serve on Extended Supervision of 6 months. This sentence is IMPOSED & STAYED and the Court places the Defendant on Probation for 2 years with conditions:
--Complete a Certified Batterer's Intervention Program
--AODA Assessment & Follow-through with any recommended treatment, per Agent
--To undergo any other assessment, treatment or counseling as per Agent
--To obtain/maintain employment and/or education program, per Agent
--No Contact with Margaret Warichak except for purposes of family court proceedings and for child placement arrangments of SW (dob: 6/21/01) and as otherwise expressly approved by Agent and Margaret
--No acts/threats of violence towards anyone
--To pay costs of $268
--To pay $100 dometic abuse surcharge
--To pay $250 DNA Surcharge
--To submit DNA Sample upon demand

If revoked: The Court finds that the Defendant is NOT eligible for the Challenge Incarceration Program (Boot Camp) and IS eligible for the Substance Abuse Program. 
If revoked: The Court gives 1 day credit for time already served.
